  "body": "*Description*:\r\nA per listener time out doesn't work well in iptables-redirect-to listener.\r\nFor example:\r\nFor server-first -packet protocol filter chain: a immediate timeout is preferred\r\nFor TLS expected filter chain: it is expected to be infinity timeout\r\n\r\nI propose adding a L4 address based timeout in sniffer listener filter (tls_inspector)\r\n```\r\nTimeouts: \r\n- matcher:\r\n   port: 3306 #mysql server first protocol \r\n  timeout: 0.0000001s\r\n- matcher: {} \r\n  timeout: 100000000s\r\n```\r\nAlternative solution:\r\n  list of port for infinity timeout, and a list of port for immediate timeout",
